default4default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLifetime inequalities of income, education, employment, health and gender are likely to increase with age.
default 
defaultIssues of equality and equity are therefore essential to the wellbeing of older people with disabilities, as they are to othe
defaultr age groups. Tackling inequalities through policy, practice and monitoring is therefore crucial to sustaining development progress and improv
defaulting the wellbeing and capabilities of current and future generations of older people. 
