defaultPoverty in old 
defaultage has a strong gender dimension. Older women are more likely to lose their partner, and less likely to remarry. Lower education levels and the need to combine work with childcare means that women are more likely to work in the informal sector
default and
default are oft
defaulten paid less than men
default, with the result that they are likely to have lower pension income in old
defaulter
default age
default. WHO has found that particular groups of older women are more at risk of poverty in all countries, including those who are widowed, divorced or with disab
defaultilities, and those caring for grandchildren and children orphaned by AIDS.
default Older women may be subject to extreme sexual violence and encounter discrimination and exclusion on account of their age and gender.
