defaultIn 2011, the first-ever High-level Meeting on Non-communicable Diseases recognised ageing as one of the four drivers of non-communicable diseases (NCDs). NCDs are the leading cause of death and 
defaultdisability worldwide, in 2010 accounting for 34.5 million of the 52.8 million deaths worldwide, with 80 per cent of these deaths occurring in the poorest countries
default.
default Some 75 per cent of deaths from NCDs in low
default-
default and middle-income countries occur in people o
defaultver 60.
default The 2011 
defaultWorld report on disability
